This article is a transcript of a press briefing by White House Press Secretary Jay Carney. During the briefing, Carney answered questions about various topics including the President's reaction to the town hall between Governor Romney and Paul Ryan, the relationship between the US and Israel, the situation in Afghanistan, and the President's views on women's rights and tax policies. Carney also addressed reports about the sentence given to Bo Xilai's wife in China and the comments made by Missouri Senate candidate Congressman Akin. The briefing concluded with a question about the recent killings of US servicemembers in Afghanistan.